T*
(GPT-5.4 or Claude Opus 4.6 or Gemini 3.1 Pro or Qwen3.5-35B-A3B. An LLM is a machine learning) Tj
T*
(model that can complete a sentence of text. Give the model the phrase "the cat sat on the " and) Tj
T*
(it will \(almost certainly\) suggest "mat" as the next word in the sentence. As these models get) Tj
T*
(larger and train on increasing amounts of data, they can complete more complex sentences - like) Tj
T*
("a python function to download a file from a URL is def download_file\(url\): ". LLMs don't) Tj
T*
(actually work directly with words - they work with tokens. A sequence of text is converted into) Tj
T*
(a sequence of integer tokens, so "the cat sat on the " becomes [3086, 9059, 10139, 402, 290,) Tj
T*
(220] . This is worth understanding because LLM providers charge based on...) Tj
